episodes.title: Andrew taken off UK peerage roll in step to remove titles
episodes.description:
Andrew Mountbatten Windsor no longer appears on the official roll of the peerage in the UK, marking a key step in formally removing his titles.

Buckingham Palace said his name had been struck from the roll after King Charles III took the dramatic decision to formally strip his brother of his Prince and Duke of York titles and HRH style, a move that effectively ends his public life.

episodes.description:
Britain's King Charles has stripped his younger brother Andrew of his title of prince and forced him out of his home by Windsor Castle, Buckingham Palace said, punishing him over his ties to the late sex offender Jeffrey Epstein.

episodes.title: The unveiling of Opus Dei | Upfront with Katie Hannon
episodes.description:
The Financial Times recently ran an extraordinary story about what life was like inside the secretive Catholic organisation Opus Dei for it’s lowest status members – who are known as assistant numeraries.

Margaret Joyce is from a family of 16 who was first introduced to Opus Dei when she was just 10 years old while at a weekly cookery club. By age 14 she believed she had a vocation and was working for Opus Dei at weekends and school holidays. She began working for them full time once she did her inter cert and moved into the Opus Dei centre at age 16. 

Opus Dei provided the following statement in relation to the interview with Margaret Joyce: https://www.rte.ie/news/upfront/2024/0422/1445074-opus-dei-statement-in-relation-to-interview-by-former-member/

episodes.description:
